Tyson's gloves barely nipped his ears and he fell down,  Tyson was putting his big heavy body behind all his jabs and punches, so even though he doesn't have the biggest punches,  with all that weight and muscles behind them hands,  it's enough to do damage,  and push Wilder around. snippet.textDisplay: My god, Wilder's footwork was less than amateurish. I wasn't paying very close attention to them during the fight, but even before his equilibrium went, he was crossing his feet over way too much. A lot of praise in the comments for Fury's coach (and rightfully so), but not much mention of the fact that Wilder's team apparently did nothing to prepare him for any kind of pressure. Once Fury knew Wilder couldn't throw off the back foot, the fight became a joke. If Wilder wants to come back, sack every single person in his team and go back to fundamentals so he can set up the right hand.
